I made this last year at Thanksgiving, and I've been asked to make it again this year. Even guests who thought they did not like beets liked these. This recipe is well balanced and results in a subtly flavorful mix of beets, horseradish and cream. The sautéed greens provide complementary taste, texture and color; don't omit them. A great side dish.

