Rating: 4
I love beets and this was a great way to prepare them. I increased the horseradish cream by a third and used it as an accompaniment to the Standing Rib Roast on this site, as an option for those who didn't want the au jus. One addition - a little mayonnaise to the cream as the sour cream mixture seemed to need something. I also quartered the beets rather than slicing them. The greens added a nice presentation and were delicious.

Rating: 3
Amazing flavours! Unfortunately, my beet leaves were badly wilted and far from nice, so I subbed with rainbow chard which yielded a colourful dish. Loved the horseradish cream! Think it would be a tasty topping for baked potatoes too, especially if served with beef. Instead of chives, I liberally garnished with fresh minced dill as it pairs so well with both beets and chard. Mmmmm, such a delicious and attractive way to make and serve beets which are so often overlooked and underused. Enjoy!

Rating: 3
You can roast the beets in foil on the grill if you don't want to heat up your kitchen. Medium beets (or large beets quartered) take about 40 minutes on my gas grill, at the lowest temp. setting (tho I do preheat the grill at the highest temp. for about 5 minutes).

